German Günther Bauer in "Flamenco-People" alternates the theatrical nature of some shots with singers, dancers and guitarists on stage with the lesser-known side of these masters.
With this objective, the photographer offers an original iconography of flamenco, capturing it from different visual angles.
The exhibition, included in the programming of the Flamenco Photography Month, reflects the international importance of this dance, which is growing every day", explains the artist and makes it clear that in "Flamenco-People" it could also be ordinary people, but by seeing the photos, the observer realizes that they are not the typical images of artists, performers or performers on stage.
These people portrayed "on the street" are "artists capable of conveying passion, sadness, joy when they are on stage... and capture the audience.
