Because their personality and character are inside.
What I was interested in was creating an intimate atmosphere that would allow me to capture the personality of the great flamenco players with my camera".
With a passion for the "Cante de las Minas" festival, Bauer began a long journey in 1997 to portray singers, guitarists or dancers using a plate camera.
They are portraits that, because of the type of machine and the material, remind of classical photography.
The application of different stylistic techniques breaks with the traditional principles of image, giving the photo modernity, according to an idea that reflects Bauer's own conception of flamenco: "A music with very traditional roots that evolves and is able to surprise every day".
Not the dance, the singing or the playing itself, but the artist's personality, his character, capable of capturing the audience with his art.
