Industrial prices continue to rise
National industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0,1% compared to the previous month, by 12,9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Hungarian Central Statistical Institute.
The prices of the export sales of the industry reported in July 2008 were higher than 1,1% and fell by 3,9% compared to the previous year.
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were higher by 0,7% compared to the previous month and by 3,2% compared to a year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales in the previous month increased only by 0,1%.
The domestic sales prices of the manufacturing sector also increased by a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The largest price increase in August 2008 was in the leather and footwear processing sector (2,8%), especially bags and belts, with 4,6% and footwear production with a monthly increase of 2,5%.
The high price level of plastic and chemical raw materials caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the product and chemical sector.
Prices decreased in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a lesser extent in the wood processing sector (0.1%).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing remained the same.
In other sectors of the manufacturing industry, prices increased by between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water sector, prices increased by 0,3% in August in industrial domestic sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in gas prices by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared to 12 months, the largest increase in domestic sales of the processing industry was in the oil products processing sector (32.4%).
In the manufacturing sector of metalworking products, prices increased by 13.2%, and by 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco, which represent a decisive factor.
Prices decreased in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the electrical equipment and machinery industry (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the manufacturing industry, the rate of price increases varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
Overall, in the manufacturing industry prices rose by 10.2% in the previous year.
The prices of the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded last year's prices by 18.7%.
In the domestic sales of the target groups of sectors, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the consumer goods sector prices increased by 0.3%, in the energy and after-use sectors prices remained unchanged from the previous month.
In August 2008, the biggest increase in prices was observed in the energy and subsequent use sector (16,8%), compared to the same month last year.
In the sectors producing consumer goods, the increase was 6.8%, and for investment goods, a decrease of 1.4%.
Industrial export sales prices in FUR increased by 1.1% in August compared to the previous month, decreasing by 3.9% in 12 months.
