Listening to music at high volume for an extended period of time using portable musical devices such as Mp3 players can cause permanent hearing damage.
The European Commission, in a communiqué in Brussels, quoted the opinion of the European Union's Scientific Committee on Emerging and Recently Identified Health Risks (CSRSeri), published today.
"This scientific opinion", the note reads, "shows that 5-10 percent of those who, for a period of at least five years, listen to music with portable musical instruments weekly for more than an hour a day while holding the loudspeaker risk permanent hearing loss".
